-Javascript can change HTML content.
-one of the many javascript HTML methods is getElementById().
-finds an HTML element with id and changes the element content.
-Example:
           <html>
           <head>
           <title><title>
           </head>
           <body>
           <p id="demo">What is felix doing?</p>
           <button type="button" onlick='document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML ="he is learning javascript">Check_IT</button>
           </body>
           </html>
-Javascript can change the HTML attributes values.
-Example:
             <html>
             <head>
             <title></title>
             </head>
             <body>
             <button onlick="document.getElementById('myImage').src='pic.gif'">on</button>
             <img id='myImage'>
                  src='pic.gif'
                  style='height:100px;
                         width:40px'
             </body>
             </html>
-Javascript can change the HTML font for example;
            <body>
            <p id="dem02">i can change my font</p>
            <button onlick="getElementById('demo2').style.fontSize='30px'>click me'</button>
            </body>
-It can display or show html.
         <body>
         <p id="demon3" style="display:none">I can be seen</p>
         <button onlick='getElementById("demo3").style.display="block">Click Here</button>
         </body>
 
 
 
 
 Javascript tag
 -------------------
 -a) script tag
 ------------------
 -used in html to insert codes.
      <script> html codes </script>
      <body>
      <p id='demo'></p>
      <script>
      document.getElementById('demo').innerHTML='demo';
      </script>
      </body>
      
 Javascript functions
 --------------------
 -Block of code that can be executed when called.
 -Called when event occurs, like when the user click a button.
 
 -Script can be placed in the body or header section of an html page or both.
 -Placing the function in the header section of the html page. It can be invocked when the button is clicked.
            <head>
            <script>
            function.myFunction(){
             document.ElementById('demo1').innerHTML ='page changed';
             }
             </script>
             </head>
             <body>
             <p id='demo1'>new page</p>
             <button type="button" onlick="myfunction()">Check_Out</button>
             </body>
 
 -Javascript function can be placed in the body section on an HTML page.
              <body>
              <p id="demo">a page</p>
              <button type="button" onclick="myFunction()">try it</button>
              <script>
              function myFunction(){
              document.getElementById('demo').innerHTML="new page;
              }
              </script>
              </body>
              
-External javascript. It can be placed in external files.
-The files have the file extension .js
-Put the name of the script file in the src(source) attribute of a <script> tag.
     <script src="myScript.js"></script>
-External script reference can be placed in the <head> or <body>
-External javascript has advantage that includes:
             -It separates HTML and code.
             -Makes HTML and Javascript easier to read and maintain.
             -cached javascript  files can speed up page loads.
 -Can be referenced with a full URL or with a path relative to the current web page.
 -Javascript display possibilities:
           -writing into an HTML element, using innerHTML.
           -Writing into  the HTML output using document.write()
           -writting into an alert box, using the window.alert()
           -Writting into the browswe console, using console.log()
 -document.getElementById(id) method is used to access an html element.
 -id attribute defines the html element.
 -The innerHTML propert defines the html content.
     
        
      
